title.narrative: OUTPUT 5.4: CROSS-CUTTING ISSUES

description.narrative: Output 5.4: Strategies to address cross-cutting issues related to child rights are developed and applied, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 5 - Programme Effectiveness: Country programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards for achieving results for children

description.narrative: Strengthened capacities for development and humanitarian contexts across sectors at national, county and sub county levels, including implementing partners for the application of multi-pronged C4D strategies (evidence generation, social mobilization and community engagement, behaviour and social change policy guidelines/standards), has resulted in evidence informed integrated C4D strategies. This has resulted in increased knowledge, demand for, utilization of services, participation and adoption of optimal caregiving practices, in focused counties. Anchoring community engagement standards and indicators has ensured greater accountability to affected populations during emergencies | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
